description:
"Global Holotropic Breathwork Day April 14th"

On April 14th, thousands of people all over the world will be breathing together.

In Stockholm, there will be a one day workshop to join and connect with the global Holotropic Breathwork family.

It is a great opportunity for those who have never tried Holotropic Breathwork before
and would like to experience a shorter version of a regular workshop.

This workshop requires pre registration to attend.

You are all warmly welcome.

"Through Healing Ourselves, We are Healing the Earth and the Rest of the Universe"


For more information about Holotropic Breathwork, please see below:

Do you have a wish to develop your spirituality?

Do you have a wish to develop your intuition and your consciousness?

Have you experienced difficult traumas in your life and have been searching for a way to heal yourself holistically; psychologically, physically, and spiritually?

Are you currently going through a life crises and seek for deep inner wisdom and insights?

If your answer is ”yes” to one or more of these questions, there is a strong possibility that you could benefit from Holotropic Breathwork. You don’t need any previous experience of Holotropic Breathwork to be able to participate in a workshop. You don’t need to be an educated psychotherapist, psychiatrist, or such either.

What is Holotropic Breathwork?

The word ”holotropic” derives from the Greek words ”holos”=whole and trepein= to move towards which means moving towards wholeness.

Holotropic Breathwork is based on 50 years of extensive research within psychological, psychotherapeutical, and a spiritual framework and has been developed by psychiatrist and psychotherapist Stanislav Grof (MD) and his wife Christina Grof. Stanislav Grof is one of the cofounders of Transpersonal Psychology since 1969 and is one of its foremost theoretics.

Important parts of Holotropic Breathwork is driving music, focused energy release work, sharing circle, and creative mandala drawings. All these parts facilitate for us opening up our own inner potential to reach deep physical, psychological and spiritual healing.

One could say that Holotropic Breathwork in this way creates a bridge between the psyche, the body and the soul and therefore is a holistic way of healing oneself.

Kajsa Söderlund was certified by Grof Transpersonal Training 2001 and offers workshops in holotropic breathwork in a loving, supportive and safe environment.
name: Stan Grof's Holotropic Breathwork in Stockholm

description:
Learn the ancient qigong practice Falun Dafa in Uppsala <br>If you are looking for a natural way to reduce stress, increase energy and mental clarity, join us for some peaceful Falun Dafa qigong exercises on Sundays 11 o’clock.
We are a group of Falun Dafa practitioners in Uppsala who have each benefitted in very personal ways from the practice, and we look forward to share the benefits of Falun Dafa with others. <br>The classes are suitable for all ages and levels of experience, and are always free of charge.

Falun Dafa (also known as Falun Gong) is an ancient Chinese qigong practice for cultivating the mind and body. Cultivation of the mind/heart are guided by the universal principles of
<br>• Zhen (true, truth, truthfulness) <br>• Shan (compassion, benevolence, kindness, goodness) <br>• Ren (forbearance, tolerance, endurance, self-control) <br>Cultivation of the body is done through practicing the five gentle exercises, one of which is a sitting meditation. The exercises and meditation work on the energy circulation of the body, opening the energy channels to allow natural purification of the body over time. With the combination of easy-to-learn exercises and universal principles, this holistic way of life is renowned for its incredible impact on health and approach to balancing modern day stresses. <br>All Falun Gong materials, including books and exercise instructions are available for free download at www.falundafa.org

Many who cultivate Falun Dafa experience a range of benefits, including: <br>- increased energy and vitality <br>- relief from stress and anxiety <br>- long-term health benefits <br>- inner harmony and spiritual perfection <br>- answers to the meaning of life

Come and try it for yourself!

Wear comfortable clothing, we have mats for everyone to sit on. Our place is suitable for atleast 25 people so bring a friend!

---

Lär dig den uråldriga qigongmetoden Falun Dafa i Uppsala

Om du letar efter ett naturligt sätt att minska stress, öka energi och mental klarhet kom då och lär dig Falun Dafa qiqgongövningar på Söndagar kl 11. Vi är en grupp Falun Dafa-utövare i Uppsala som var och en har gynnats på väldigt personliga sätt av metoden, och vi vill gärna dela med oss av fördelarna med Falun Dafa med er.

Falun Dafa och övningarna är lämpliga för alla, oavsett ålder och tidigare erfarenhet, och är alltid gratis.

Falun Dafa (kallas även Falun Gong) är en uråldrig kinesisk qigong-metod för att kultivera kropp och sinne. Kultiveringen av hjärtat och sinnet vägleds av de universella principerna:

• Zhen (sanning, sant, sanningsenlighet) <br>• Shan (godhet, medkänsla, välvilja, vänlighet) <br>• Ren (tålamod, tolerans, uthållighet, självkontroll)

Kultivering av kroppen görs genom att utföra de fem mjuka qigongövningarna, varav en är sittande meditation. Övningarna och meditationen stärker kroppens energimekanismer och öppnar energikanalerna för att tillåta naturlig rening av kroppen över tid. Med kombinationen av lättlärda övningar och universella principer är detta holistiska sätt att leva på känt för att hjälpa utövaren att uppnå ett harmoniskt balanserat liv i det höga tempot i dagens samhälle. <br>Alla Falun Dafa-material, inklusive böcker och övningsinstruktioner finns tillgängliga för gratis nedladdning på www.falundafa.org

Många som kultiverar Falun Dafa upplever en rad fördelar, såsom:

- Ökad energi och vitalitet <br>- Minskad stress och ångest <br>- Långsiktiga hälsofördelar <br>- Inre harmoni och andlig fulländning <br>- Svar på livets mening

Kom och prova på själv!

Kom i bekväma kläder, vi har mattor för alla att sitta på. Våran lokal är lämplig för minst 25 personer, så ta gärna med en vän!
name: Learn the ancient qigong practice Falun Dafa

description:
We are all volunteers of a Charity organisation and have many years of experience in offering free Sahaja Yoga Meditation classes. All the meetings and classes are free of any charge. Each week we go through simple meditation techniques, often with guided meditations to help reduce stress and achieve the peace of true meditation. We share tips on how to help stay in balance during the day and how to meditate at home. The meditation is based on connecting with the inner chakras (energy centres) and balancing the subtle body. The tradition and aims of meditation are explained which in essence is to be in the present with no mental activity or thoughts about the past or the future. The classes are designed to help those attending get into a genuine meditative state, which can be felt tangibly. It is quite effortless and spontaneous. The free classes feature introductory talks, videos, practical workshops and general question and answer opportunities, making them perfect for seekers trying to establish a state of yoga.

The idea is that you don't do yoga - you Achieve Yoga!

Sahaja Yoga Meditation is a simple technique. It helps those who enjoy it, reduce stress and increase wellness. It brings better focus and helps people become more centered and better balanced. Anyone can do it.

Founded by Shri Mataji Nirmala Devi, Sahaja Yoga Meditation is a world wide movement for peace and self awakening. All across the globe, many are seeking new sources of energy. Meanwhile, the most transformative energy of all is hiding in plain sight, within us. It's natural, sustainable, and infinitely renewable. It's called inner kundalini energy. And everyone already has it — everyone! It is often likened to an inner feminine or motherly energy which automatically knows about us and what is needed to help us restore balance and harmony within our subtle being. It works spontaneously, effortlessly, organically and cannot be paid for.

www.sahajayoga.se

www.freemeditation.com

www.sahajayoga.org/worldwidecontacts

You can also find us on Facebook www.facebook.com/sahajayogasweden

description:
Learn to Meditate! Ishayas Ascension is ancient, simple and effortless practice for anyone. Ascension techniques are tools for meditation, inner understanding and expansion of consciousness. They are based on fundamental truths, Praise, Gratitude and Love. Because that is so, we don`t need to believe they they work.

We teachers of Ascension love to share this practice. This group is started for anyone interested to know more about it. To learn Ishayas Ascension we offer weekend format called First Sphere course. For coming courses in Sweden we will give information in this group. If you have wish to have weekend workshop near by you - please contact with teachers of Ascension.


Whenever life becomes hectic or crazy or you feel stressed out, you can Ascend – And from Ascending return to silence, to peace, to innocence... to the present moment.

The Art of Ascension is not a belief system, it is not a new religion or an old religion; it is a series of mechanical techniques that give both the mind and body exactly what they need/desire to work in optimal efficiency.

To explain how that works and what happens is a lot more difficult than the actual process of it happening while we are Ascending. However, essentially what happens is the accumulation of stress or fear, doubt and limited energy is washed away and we are left with a free and clear mind/body to approach our lives in appreciation, gratitude, love and compassion.

It is a very simple practice. No Belief is required for it to work...no mantra, no effort, no control. It is that simple and incredibly effective.

This Ancient Teaching is so effective it can be practiced not only as a meditation but also with the eyes open in the hustle and bustle of daily activities.

Since we have Introductory Talks, Meditation Workshops and Meetings around Finland and the world, please also visit our web site for updated schedules.

http://www.ishayasworldwide.com/


https://youtu.be/Td3QPDIVhZY

description: Are you a "scanner"? - You have creative ideas all the time, whether it’s for a book, a TV show, an art project, a website, a business, starting a movement, creating a brand, or a renovation project - You love to learn about new subjects and ideas but then quickly move on to something else - You have lots of seemingly unrelated interests - Trying to choose between all your ideas, interests and projects seems impossible and stresses you out - The thought of concentrating on one job or business for the rest of your life fills you with dread - You start lots of projects but don’t always finish them If you are like this, you may be a "scanner" (a term coined by US author Barbara Sher). I am definitely a scanner too. Scanners have a reluctance to commit to just one thing ("what if I pick the wrong option?") and a tendency to abandon projects before completion ("look, something more interesting, let's do that!"). This doesn’t have to be a problem, but today's society doesn't exactly promote our way of being. Let's support each other and stimulate our creativity! We meet once a month in central Stockholm, usually a bar or a coffee place. Nothing fancy. We exchange ideas. Both to get creative feedback and to feel supported in the everyday life of a scanner!
name: Stockholm Scanners

description:
Mindful awareness can be defined as paying attention to present moment experiences with openness, curiosity, and a willingness to be with what is. It is an excellent antidote to the stresses of modern times. It invites us to stop, breathe, observe, and connect with one's inner experience In this group, you will learn Mindful concepts that include:

An Overview of Mindfulness Mindfulness of the Body

Obstacles to Mindfulness Mindfulness to help with Physical Pain

Working with Difficult Emotions

Cultivating Positive Emotions

Working with Difficult Thoughts

Mindful Interactions

You will also learn a variety of mindfulness practices to discover which practice is useful to you. Practices taught include: Sitting meditation, eating meditation, daily life meditations, relational mindfulness, walking meditation, standing meditation, movement meditation and practices to develop positive emotions

category.name: health/wellbeing
description: I have found nothing better than a weekly 24 hour fast on water for the mind, body, and soul. Fasting is a challenge. A support group is a big plus. Fasting will change your life. I have been doing a weekly 24-36 hour fast for 7 years straight not missing a week. I have learned a lot of good tricks to make the most of your fasting experience which I can share you. Want to transform and super charge your life? Allow you mind and body a break from the heavy work of thinking about,preparing, digesting and eliminating food. Many people go on these torturous 7 to 40 day fasts and then go right back to the eating habits before the fast vowing they will never do that again. I am not against these fast but I believe consistency is the real game changer. A consistent weekly fast will change the way you think about food and prepare you for the longer fasts which can be managed more more easily when your body adapts to the small weekly breaks. Eventually on the fast day your body does not want to eat. It enjoys the break. But that will take some time to develop that attitude. At first it can be hard and a support group is a big help.
name: Stockholm Fasting Meetup

description:
What really motivates you? What makes you get up in the morning and do what you do? In this group we discuss, compare and evaluate different motivational frameworks with special focus on Reiss Motivation Profile.

The motivational research by the American Professor Steven Reiss forms the scientific basis of the Reiss Motivation Profile. Using numerous studies with thousands of trial subjects he identified a total of 16 psychological basic desires which every human being possesses. These basic desires must be satisfied in order that we feel our lives to be meaningful. They are moulded by our genes and experiences in childhood and adolescence, remain largely constant throughout our lives in accordance with previous perceptions and thus give us permanent orientation.

As with every other scientific procedure in personality or motivational psychology, you have to decide entirely as an individual which indicators from the results are important or meaningful for you – and which not. The following questions may help you: How well does each basic desire characteristic describe my actual need? At which places do the statements apply particularly well, and in which points do I not recognise myself? How do I live each basic desire in my day-to-day life?

These are questions that all people should be able to answer to be able to fill their lives with Value based happiness.

If you are interested in living your life (and worklife) with greater fulfillment and joy, join us in the discussion at the next meetup.
name: Motivation in life and business - Stockholm

description:
Rangjung Yeshe Sangha Sverige is a meditation and Buddhist studies group practicing under the guidance of Tulku Chökyi Nyima Rinpoche, Abbot of Ka-Nying monastery based in Kathmandu, Nepal. 

Our group studies and practices Buddhism with a focus on Mahayana and Vajrayana in the Tibetan tradition. 

We are meeting every Sunday between 14.30 and 16.30 at the Drom Tonpa Center on Södermalm, Stockholm, to practice meditation, watch videos and documentaries, discuss, try Qi Gong, drink tea, and cook momos and other Himalaya specialties :) Everyone is welcome to join, even if you have never practiced meditation before. We will be happy to assist and guide you. 

All our meetups are free, we nevertheless appreciate a small donation (20-40 SEK) to contribute to the rent of the place.

You can read more information about us on our website here.

Welcome!

description:
Har du rest utåt tillräckligt? Är det dags för en resa inåt?

På Mindful Mondays vänder vi uppmärksamheten inåt för att på ett kul, nyfiket och ibland utmanande sätt ta reda på mer om oss själva. Vad vill du? Vad vill du inte? Vilka tankar och idéer har du om dig själv och andra? Stämmer de? Vad får dig avslappnad och trygg? Vad får dig att känna dig levande och upprymd?

Mindful Mondays är till stor del upplevelsebaserat och vi kommer att utforska oss själva genom övningar. Förutom att ge nya insikter är vår ambition att måndagen ska bli en kul och avslappnande start på veckan! Du kommer alltid att få med dig konkreta verktyg att använda i vardagen.

Varje måndag berör vi ett nytt tema och det går lika bra att komma vid ett tillfälle som på samtliga.

Inga förkunskaper krävs, bara en nyfikenhet att lära sig mer om sig själv.

För frågor nå oss på:

Niklas Heckscher 0736-006050 niklas@heckscher.nu

Magnus Quensel 0709-950584 magnus@quensel.nu

VILKA ÄR NIKLAS OCH MAGNUS?

Niklas har en bakgrund som lärare och har under halva sitt liv tränat idrottare på elitnivå. Förutom lång erfarenhet av coaching och idrottspsykologi har han de senaste åren gått flera kurser inom personlig utveckling.

Magnus har under 15 års tid gått flertalet kurser inom terapi, coaching och personlig utveckling i olika länder. Han har nyligen tillsammans med Niklas avslutat en diplomerad utbildning till Mindfulnessinstruktör. Magnus jobbar även med entreprenörskap och driver ett hotell i Spanien.

Mindful Mondays är början av ett nytt projekt som kommer att utvecklas även utanför måndagar med olika events, resor och happenings - för människor som vill lära känna sig själva - tillsammans med andra.
name: Mindful Mondays: Meet yourself - with others

description:
INTRO:

We offer classes, courses and retreats in Meditation & Modern Buddhism. Our classes are suitable for everyone. You do not have to be Buddhist to take part in or benefit from the classes. 

Most of our classes are held by Buddhist monk Kelsang Jangdom who has over ten years of experience practising Buddhism. Our classes consist of a practical and inspiring talk on integrating Buddha's ancient wisdom into our modern lives and two relaxing guided meditations. 

Everyone is welcome at our classes - and we mean it!

LANGUAGES:

We offer activities in both English and Swedish. It says at the top of each activity which language the Meetup is in. 

VIDEO:

Here is a short video about us:

https://vimeo.com/149410271

https://vimeo.com/149410271

MEDITATION:

The purpose of meditation is to make our mind calm and peaceful.

If our mind is peaceful, we will be free from worries and mental discomfort, and so we will experience true happiness; but if our mind is not peaceful, we will find it very difficult to be happy, even if we are living in the very best conditions.

If we train in meditation, our mind will gradually become more and more peaceful, and we will experience a purer and purer form of happiness. Eventually, we will be able to stay happy all the time, even in the most difficult circumstances.

Usually we find it difficult to control our mind. It seems as if our mind is like a balloon in the wind – blown here and there by external circumstances. If things go well, our mind is happy, but if they go badly, it immediately becomes unhappy. For example, if we get what we want, such as a new possession or a new partner, we become excited and cling to them tightly.

By training in meditation, we create an inner space and clarity that enables us to control our mind regardless of the external circumstances. Gradually we develop mental equilibrium, a balanced mind that is happy all the time, rather than an unbalanced mind that oscillates between the extremes of excitement and despondency.

If we train in meditation systematically, eventually we will be able to eradicate from our mind the delusions that are the causes of all our problems and suffering. In this way, we will come to experience a permanent inner peace, known as “liberation” or “nirvana”. Then, day and night in life after life, we will experience only peace and happiness.

(excerpt from How to Solve our Human Problems by Geshe Kelsang Gyatso)

description:
Are you afraid? Afraid to try out new things, meeting new people, facing new challenges, embarking on new adventures? So am I. Fear can hold us back, it can paralyze us, force us to live a boring existence and a miserable life. Fear can kill us. This group is about finding what holds us back, exploring our internal barriers and getting out there in spite of the anxiety, in spite of the fear. This group is about breaking out of our comfort zone and live a magical and exciting life. Together we'll talk about our challenges, face our fears, so that we can live ever more freely. “Often we think, »I’ll do it when I am not so afraid.« But in reality, it works the other way round. The 'doing it' comes before the fear goes away. The only way to get rid of the fear of doing something is to go out and do it.“ Susan Jeffers (Feel the fear and do it anyway)

Let's get together, face challenges and crush our comfort zone. To know more about this life philosophy, watch this video and let Till inspire you the way he inspired me to just go for it and try something adventurous:

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HtDkg3Xwn7U

Links: http://www.facebook.com/comfortzonecrusher and http://www.comfortzonecrusher.com/

description:
iMeditate Stockholm is a city-wide movement offering group meditation opportunities to empower people to lead better lives. iMeditate Stockholm gives you an opportunity to breathe, meditate and meet with like-minded people and collectively focus on peaceful thinking and personal growth

iMeditate Stockholm is like a running group for your mind. It helps you to re-energize and grow your meditation skills in group gatherings. It is a campaign that aims to increase awareness of the powerful benefits of meditation as a practical way to recharge and rejuvenate every day. During the iMeditate session, we will start with yoga, followed by some pranayama (breathing techniques), meditation and end with fika.

iMeditate Stockholm is aimed at manifesting the vision of the Art of Living, which aims to create a violence-free and stress-free society. It offers stress relief and personal development programmes that benefit over a million people in more than 150 countries globally. The founder is Sri Sri Ravi Shankar, a humanitarian and peace leader, whose vision is to have a stress free and violence free society. His overall vision is to bring peace to the world. https://www.artofliving.org/

category.name: health/wellbeing
description:
Эта группа - для всех, Эта группа - для всех, кто готов находить нестандартные ходы в своей жизни, чтобы выбраться из болота обстоятельств, кто не хочет повторять ни своих, ни чужих ошибок в жизни . Кто готов учиться сам и помогать учиться другим не только на пролитых слезах, но и на своих и чужих победах. Кто готов взглянуть на любую, самую трудную ситуацию с такой стороны, откуда виден незаметный ранее выход.
В группе приветствуются те, кто хотят разобраться в жизненных успехах и неудачах, для того чтобы построить свою новую жизнь по лучшему, успешному сценарию без боли и страданий.
Мы встречаемся, чтобы обсудить всевозможные вызовы в сфере здоровья, взаимоотношений, социальной, культурной, духовной жизни и найти наилучшие выходы из трудных жизненных ситуаций.
При этом, знания нетрадиционной, холистической медицины и психологии приветствуются, а знатоки особенностей женской души будут также очень уместны на наших встречах.
Мы всегда рады встрече с людьми, только выходящими на жизненные просторы, и тем, кто «съел собаку» на жизненных невзгодах, молодым энтузиастам и разочарованным пессимистам перестроечных времен.
Наши встречи, а также возможные тренинги и курсы, проводятся на русском, и поэтому для участников важно базовое знание русского языка.
Мы встречаемся, как правило, еженедельно. Время и место каждой встречи сообщается отдельно.
Добро пожаловать ВСЕ, КТО ИЩЕТ ВЫХОД! А ВЫХОД ЕСТЬ ВСЕГДА!
----------------------------

This group is for all those who are ready to find unconventional moves in their lives in achieving their goals, who do not want to repeat their own or other people's mistakes in life. Who is ready to learn by himself and help others to learn not only on shed tears, but also on their own and others' victories. For those, who is ready to look at any, the most difficult situation from such a side, from where it´s possible to see an inconspicuous earlier exit.
The group welcomes those who want to understand life's successes and failures in order to build their new life for a better, successful scenario without pain and suffering.
We meet to discuss all kinds of challenges in the field of health, relationships, social, cultural, spiritual life and find the best ways out of difficult life situations.
At the same time, knowledge of non-traditional, holistic medicine and psychology is welcome, and experts on the features of the “female soul” will be very appropriate at our meetings.
We are always glad to meet people who are just going out into the realms of life, and those who knows life's misfortunes inside out, young enthusiasts and disillusioned pessimists of “perestroika times”.
Our meetings, as well as possible trainings and courses, held in Russian, and therefore the basic knowledge of the Russian language is important for participants.
We meet, as a rule, on weekly basis. The time, place and subject of each meeting reports separately.
We welcome everyone who is looking for a way out! THE WAY OUT EXISTS ALWAYS!
name: Russian Meetings: The Unique Chance

category.name: health/wellbeing
description:
Hi!

I am a family man. I have a steady job. I have a comfy home. I work at least 40 hours per week. At the end of every month I pay my bills and providing my family as much as i can. Always looking forward for the 4-5 weeks vacation every year or every weekend. The rest of the time i am mostly tired and sometimes stressed out. Trying to make the most of the time left each day. <br>I am also thankful for what i have but im not happy or content about giving my time away. Time I want to spend with my son. Time I want to spend on what really matters to me. I give 8-10 hours everyday to one or several companies that is not made for my own well being. I work for someone else to forfill someonelse dreams. <br>What about my dreams, what am i willing to do for making them come true? Have you asked yourself this question? There is more of life than what society teaches you. So I have decided and started a journey towards more freedom and time! <br>Freedom and time is my most valuable assets. I am not willing to trade that away anymore for this "safty" way of living that society slowly waggles you into. If you feel or can relate on what i feel. I'll gladly meet you. To inspire you and to be inspired by you. I am confident in whoever you are, you are an amazing person with great ideas and potential! I dare you to leave your comfortzone and to have an open mind. Lets meet up! <br>I know there is huge success within reach, and this is reached far better and faster together! Best regards / Toni
name: End "rat race". Together for more!
organizer.name: Toni Wigren

description:
This is a group for women who are interested in having a happy, healthy relationship with food. 

If you're struggling with feeling out of control or frustrated with your eating, want to learn what foods work best for you, or want fun + friendly support from other ladies who understand - then this meetup is for you.

This is for you if:
- You're a woman (or identify as one)
- You want to create and maintain a happy relationship with food
- You struggle with binge eating, emotional eating, stress eating, or just feeling horrible about how you eat
- You're interested in nutrition
- You want to lose/gain/maintain weight in a way that works for your body and your life
- You want to give + get help, support, and advice

This group is not for:
- Trying to sell your services or stuff
- Multi-level marketing
- Therapy
- Eating disorders (you're very welcome to come, but I'm not licensed to help you with that).

What will we do?
We'll meet twice a month for fika and a chat - usually with a particular theme or focus to get us started. I'll be there with professional tips + advice, but it's not a seminar or presentation. More like a group of friends where you can get answers and support so you can move forward with creating new habits and lifestyle changes that stick.

Who am I?
I'm Samantha and I'm a certified coach and counselor who works with overeating, emotional eating, and food addiction, along with other challenges such as depression, anxiety, and motivation. I'm not selling anything in these meetups - but I may need to ask for a small joining fee if we rent a room for meetings. You can find more about me and what I do at http://livethewhole.com
name: Women's Eating Psychology + Wellness in Stockholm

description:
Viveka Khyati Yoga is a group to get together to do relaxing yoga asana's, meditate and talk about yoga philosophy and life, under the guidance of yoga teacher Annelies :)

In the summer we get together for yoga in the park. In the autumn, we will move inside to have cosy, warm and interesting indoor sessions, all at very low cost. I would like this meetup group to become a place to make real connections and practice yoga and learn together.

I have a raja yoga teacher certificate and started teaching yoga to my colleagues almost two years ago. I would now like to exchange my yoga experience with others and connect to fellow yogis. Last year I have organised some nice yoga sessions in the park already, and I hope to repeat and elaborate the gatherings this year :)

So let's all join to relax, learn and grow closer to our true selves :)

category.name: health/wellbeing
description:
Enough. Time. Wasted. 

Let's stop trying to transform ourselves and start the actual transformation!

Hi there!

You probably know what you need to do to change, transform or improve yourself, right? But you might be struggling with how you are actually going to do it, how to fit it into your life, and how to make the change permanent? Could that be it? If so, you have come to the right place! Heck, even if you don't know what you need to do you have come to the right place! We will all try to get these things figured out together!

"My current life situation is the result of my habits." 

Do you agree with this statement? If you are ready to take ownership of this fact, then you are in the perfect position to change almost every single aspect of your life you are unhappy with. (Obviously there are certain exceptions such as accidents, permanent conditions, etc, but if you are here looking to transform something it is probably not fixed, right?)

So, come on and join and we will get cracking on our transformation together - because change is HARD and a supportive environment is necessary to stay the course!

Look forward to meeting you all!
name: Stockholm Life Transformation Meetup

description:
Most of us have fleeting ideas of what we want to BE, DO or HAVE in our lives. But they remain just that: fleeting. After all, who has the time to intentionally get clear about what we want to create?
Well, everyone from Katy Perry to Ellen DeGeneres to Oprah Winfrey swears that they intentionally created outcomes by using a simple tool: Vision Boards.

A Vision Board is a way to sell your own ideas to yourself, to anchor to your dreams and to allow the magic of manifestation to work in your life. Finally!

As someone who has made my own Vision Boards (and manifested some amazing results!), I’ve learned it’s more than just slapping a picture onto a poster board. It’s about first getting clear on your authentic life, letting go of what’s in the way – and then clearly connecting with your dreams while designing a vision that calls to you.

That’s why I’m leading this CREATE YOUR LIFE VISION-BOARD WORKSHOP... to give you the space you need to intentionally define your dreams and create a Vision Board that will effortlessly attract your ideal outcomes to you!

HERE’S WHAT YOU’LL GET
* Clarity on what you really want (No more settling for someone else’s dreams)
* Space and time to map out your ideal outcomes in each area of your life
* Connection with like-minded peers (deeply connect and receive support and encouragement from other wonderful women!)
* A method to clear out the natural “gunk” that arises (Time to let go!)
* All the tools and time to create your own powerful Vision Board (You only have to bring the most favorite photo of yourself. I’ve got all the other materials you need right in the room!)
* Your very own Vision Board to take home and effortlessly attract your ideal outcomes in the months ahead.
* A full day of breathing room and dream-time. (The very thing you keep telling yourself you’ll give yourself but never do!)
name: Vision Board Workshop for Women

description:
Stockholm Community Mindfulness (also Facebook group: https://www.facebook.com/groups/1213341705477070/)  is a group/community for ANYONE who has an interest and curiosity with the theme of sustainable personal development.  This group is unique in that there is no specific guiding teacher and no specific technique - its your choice. We all meet as equals to question, share, and inspire each other to explore the open awareness we most deeply are. We give ourselves the opportunity to explore present awareness through basic observations. It is possible to then monitor how this feels, day-to-day, and gradually creates changes in our behaviors, and therefore quality of life, for the better. We can cultivate and promote a growing awareness through various types of practices, and even simply through conversations and friendships with like-minded people. Even if you never tried any kind of meditation/mindfulness practices before, or if you feel like you tried but don't understand it - this would be an welcoming community for you to explore. Even if you have already been doing one or many practices for years and years, this would still be a relevant and valuable space to gain new perspectives and/or realize some refreshed inspiration, and otherwise, why not? If you are already a teacher or coach of meditation/mindfulness/personal development: all the more reason you may be interested in being part of a broader community such as this - maybe you can meet some new people interested in what you have to share... 

We gather weekly (once or several times per week) and have a quiet sit, in chairs or cushions, and combine this with mindful conversations. Here you can meet other people interested in personal development and everything else that may go along with it. Discover new resources such as other groups, teachers, internet resources, books, retreats, courses, techniques, etc. Essentially these are open source, in-person, gatherings where we have the chance to learn from each others company and experiences. You can also simply remain quiet and observing, gaining synergy to fortify your own practice. Often people find it balancing and effective to combine solo practice with some days of sitting and practicing or talking with others about it.

**This is a FREE group, because whatever space we use will be graciously donated or sponsored. A day/time/location has not yet been determined for our weekly gatherings. The goal is to have this sorted out by mid-January so expect a message or check back for details. We hope to make it a central Stockholm location, after work hours, most likely on Monday, Tuesday or Wednesday (or multiple). 

More Details: We sit quietly for 30 minutes, followed by discussion for 30 minutes and afterward people can mingle or gather in another place for dinner/drinks/tea/whatever. People are also free to leave at any time during the hour. The silent sitting can be interspersed, perhaps, with some guided mindfulness instruction or a brief reading, or even a little movement. Or depending on the given facilitator (there will be rotating facilitators) it may be 30 minutes of only silence, but always with a brief introduction and suggestions in the beginning.  Sitting posture is relaxed, we will have chairs to sit on, so if you would like to sit on a cushion, etc please feel free to bring your own. It's not a rigid experience so people can move whenever they need to!

REFERENCES: 

We already have a growing community in Oslo over the last 7 months of over 1000 members from Meetup and the Facebook group. As of now, between 15 and 25 people come each and every Monday, as well as when we create additional gatherings during the week or weekend social gatherings. 

Community Mindfulness via Meetup.com in Oslo:  https://www.meetup.com/Oslo-Community-Mindfulness

Community Mindfulness via Facebook in Oslo: https://www.facebook.com/groups/211056846067562/

category.name: health/wellbeing
description:
"Global Holotropic Breathwork Day April 14th"

On April 14th, thousands of people all over the world will be breathing together.

In Stockholm, there will be a one day workshop to join and connect with the global Holotropic Breathwork family.

It is a great opportunity for those who have never tried Holotropic Breathwork before
and would like to experience a shorter version of a regular workshop.

This workshop requires pre registration to attend.

You are all warmly welcome.

"Through Healing Ourselves, We are Healing the Earth and the Rest of the Universe"


For more information about Holotropic Breathwork, please see below:

Do you have a wish to develop your spirituality?

Do you have a wish to develop your intuition and your consciousness?

Have you experienced difficult traumas in your life and have been searching for a way to heal yourself holistically; psychologically, physically, and spiritually?

Are you currently going through a life crises and seek for deep inner wisdom and insights?

If your answer is ”yes” to one or more of these questions, there is a strong possibility that you could benefit from Holotropic Breathwork. You don’t need any previous experience of Holotropic Breathwork to be able to participate in a workshop. You don’t need to be an educated psychotherapist, psychiatrist, or such either.

What is Holotropic Breathwork?

The word ”holotropic” derives from the Greek words ”holos”=whole and trepein= to move towards which means moving towards wholeness.

Holotropic Breathwork is based on 50 years of extensive research within psychological, psychotherapeutical, and a spiritual framework and has been developed by psychiatrist and psychotherapist Stanislav Grof (MD) and his wife Christina Grof. Stanislav Grof is one of the cofounders of Transpersonal Psychology since 1969 and is one of its foremost theoretics.

Important parts of Holotropic Breathwork is driving music, focused energy release work, sharing circle, and creative mandala drawings. All these parts facilitate for us opening up our own inner potential to reach deep physical, psychological and spiritual healing.

One could say that Holotropic Breathwork in this way creates a bridge between the psyche, the body and the soul and therefore is a holistic way of healing oneself.

Kajsa Söderlund was certified by Grof Transpersonal Training 2001 and offers workshops in holotropic breathwork in a loving, supportive and safe environment.
name: Stan Grof's Holotropic Breathwork in Stockholm

description:
Welcome to the Off the Beaten Path, a transformational travel community powered by Adventure Awake.


We are a community of seekers and wayfinders. 

We are perpetually embarking on a journey into the unknown. We yearn for new discoveries about ourselves and the world, and work to build a life that is better than good. 

We believe in addressing the whole human and we understand that we would be nothing without connection and intimacy with those around us. 

We create space for one another to practice being our authentic selves. 

We share the tools we use that PROMOTE who we truly are, UNFOLD who we want to become, EXPLORE what we what to discover about ourselves and GET CURIOUS about what we don't yet know.

We work toward being masters of our own territory so that we can be clear about our place in the world.

We have ownership and responsibility of ourselves, and are driven by our deeper purpose and cause. 

We are Citizens of the World. 

Things we like to talk about: relationship, intimacy, money, meditation, travel, adventure, career, family, parenting, education, emotional intelligence, empowerment, power, desire, purpose, personal development, leadership development, coaching, manifestation, spirituality, communication, science, connection, authenticity, consciousness and much much more.
name: Adventure Awake: Off the Beaten Path

description:
Come and join our weekly practice groups to learn more about the beautiful practice of Qigong and meditation. Qigong helps you to transform energy blockages in your body. It restores and balances your energy through simple and effective exercises and meditation. The practice of qigong (chee gong) enhances the flow of vital energy and gives you optimal health, wellness and joy. It is a form of Medical Qigong, Nei Gong and meditations, which is consisting of active exercises and meditations designed to assist you in improving your health, transformation and spiritual awakening. This practice has many health benefits including: Pain relief, increased strength and vitality, stress reduction, depression and anxiety relief and improved flexibility as well gaining a sense of contentment and recognizing your inner natural state.

You are heartily welcome and anyone can join this wonderful art of healing and transformation.

category.name: health/wellbeing
description: Mahatma Gandhi once said about meditation, "I have an extremely busy day today, and I have such little time to do everything! I need to do double the meditation to cope with it." He was one of the few who knew that meditation increases one's efficiency and productivity, and meditated every single day. ​Competition is at its highest, and being innovative and productive is more important than ever today. Employees who work hard and devote more and more time to being productive end up becoming very stressed. A stressful mind will never be productive or creative. If this was the case, most of the frustrated, stressed-out, unemployed youth would be very creative or innovative. This is not the case. Creativity and innovation can only come from a relaxed mind. Similarly, productivity can only come from deep rest. This seems contradictory. How can you rest when you have tonnes of work to complete? Just like in order to hit an arrow on a target, the arrow must first be pulled backward, in the same way, to be more efficient at work, some amount of time must be spent in meditation, i.e., doing nothing, but relaxing effortlessly. This is the key to get more work done in less time, and keep stress at bay. I Meditate Malmö is a movement empowering Malmoers to do more of the things they love by recharging through meditation: a practical way to refresh every day, invented thousands of years ago. Reinvented in 2014. 'I Meditate' is an initiative of the US Art of Living chapter. Some other cities/places where free meditation is offered under "I Meditate" are: 1. New York, USA - http://www.imeditateny.org/ 2. Calgary, Canada - http://imeditatecalgary.org/ 3. Washington DC, USA - http://imeditatedc.org/ 4. Africa - http://www.artofliving.org/i-meditate-africa 5. Gothenburg, Sweden - https://www.facebook.com/IMeditateGBG 6. Stockholm, Sweden
name: I Meditate Malmö

description:
ECO TRANCE PLANT MYSTERY is a project born in Copenhagen in 2005 out of the longing to celebrate the mysterious divine forces of Creation in a playful manner through live act music and different forms of artistic performance.


Today we are able to create music that is full of suggestive and expanding landscapes of sound, uplifting melodies and deep rhythms that easily induces states of beneficial trance and helps to attain profound and high states of consciousness. Together with the music these extraordinary states can be created and amplified with visual effects, sacred geometrical shapes, astralizing lightscapes and magic performances.


ECO TRANCE PLANT MYSTERY and our trance parties are designed to create the proper exterior conditions for you to experience a gradual deepening into uplifting and beneficial states of trance with all its benefits. For this everybody have to give up any preconceived ideas about what is dance, what is trance and what is party. Let oneself free and just be. On the dance floor all improvisations are open to serve the goal which is: to attain a beneficial state of trance through dancing and letting the music vibrate in your entire being thus allowing you to resonate with its specific uplifting energies and experience higher states of consciousness.


ECO TRANCE PLANT MYSTERY events are strictly without use of any kind of alcoholic, psychedelic or narcotic drugs. We promote health improving energetic work like yoga, meditation, bodywork, conscious sustainable lifestyle and healthy diet. It is all about getting natural high! All we use for that is music, body moves (dance), tonifying plants, aphrodisiacs, and powerful inspired and beautiful verbal suggestions - the so called 'trance inductions' - which allow all here that are open and ready to spiral up and create an unforgettable positive experience and higher states of consciousness.


The dance floor is a field of experience that has to be connected with the inside, with the heart. The dance style is any style suitable to express the inner state and to carry the mind in the proper state of superior relaxation that is the first essential condition to the mysterious states of trance. The first principle that has to be followed is to keep MOVING! Until you can feel it vibrating in your entire body, and in your mind as a tranquil euphoric inner state.


Conscious dance is an active meditation for the ones initiated to the mysteries of trance. Ecstatic dance removes limiting thoughts, prejudices and inhibitions and helps to awaken the latent life force energy in every human, known as kundalini shakti in the tradition of yoga & tantra. Every moment of life can turn into a celebration, when we learn to focus on the present moment and become aware of the mysterious dance of life. Through the state of trance the mundane can be perceived sublime and divine.

Inspiring video from one of the parties. This one is in Finland: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Mh_TAyHUBYY
name: Eco Trance Plant Mystery

description:
I am about human connection. I am already connected to many resourceful communities, groups of people and loving friends. My vision is to start a new community. You are welcome to help me do that. Together we will collaborate on how to make that happen.

The purpose of the meetup is to support one another in living life more joyfully. We meet and share of our lifes and experiences. We get more people to interact with. We also learn how to hold space for others, without needing to fix or change who they are.

You should join if you have an intention to grow personally. Your membership will help prevent the disease of isolation. So many people neglect their desire for true connection with the excuse that they are too busy. This can create lonelyness. If you want to be the listening ear for another person, you should join. If you want tools to become better at bringing more attention to your body, come and be inspired.

Your participation will allow you to be there for yourself, as you will learn how to listen to your true desires. You also get to build loving connections to others.
name: Copenhagen Life Coaching Meetup

Empowerment och livstillfredställelse

Balanced View är en snabbt växande gräsrotsrörelse som stärker människor över hela världen att vara till kraftfull nytta för alla. Genom att delta i möten och träningar kommer du att upptäcka din outtömliga kraft att vara till stor nytta för dig själv och för världen. 

Direkta resultat av träningen inkluderar:

• Fullständig mental och emotionell stabilitet

• Fullständig livstillfredställelse

• Förmågan att ta klara beslut

• Lösningsfokus

• Empowerment av styrkor, gåvor och talanger

• Harmoniska relationer

• Förmågan att leva din fulla potential i varje ögonblick.

Öppna möten/Meetups ger en utmärkt introduktion till Balanced View-träningen och är ett bra tillfälle för frågor och svar. Kvalificerade tränare och Balanced View-deltagare delar det direkta resultatet av hur det är att förlita sig på nätverket av empowerment inom Balanced View – De fyra stöttepelarna. description:
A group for everyone who wants to learn and experience heart-based meditation! 

Participate in our workshops or Introduction Courses in order to learn and experience meditation on the heart. Heartfulness offers a simple set of techniques for relaxation and meditation. It's an effective way to get relaxed, to achieve clarity in mind and to get a sense of healthy balance and well-being in your life.

description:
The most basic human right is the right to know the beneficial nature of our intelligence and empower our talents for the benefit of all. 

Balanced View is a grassroots global movement introducing a beneficial way of using our mind, complete life-satisfaction, natural leadership and flourishing through the accessible training and social network. 

The public meetings offer a clear, vital and dynamic education for our time. 

The everyday results through participation in this educational and social network are: 
- Clarity and stability regardless of circumstances 
- Easeful and effective cooperation and harmonious relationships 
- Solution focus 
- Ability to make clear and confident decisions 
- Continuous innovation and empowerment of strengths, gifts and talents 
- Spontaneous aspiration and motivation to benefit all 

We use our Meetup site simply to provide information about when and where the Meetups take place. 

If you would like more information about Balanced View, you are very welcome to drop by to a meet up, open meeting and/or to visit...

Our Website

Or to contact: balancedviewcph@gmail.com

A great place to start is to watch some introductory videos. Enjoy!

description: Ready for an insight-filled adventure? Then join The Quest, a 24-hour improvisational journey! Described by participants as “completely transformational,” The Quest is an improvisational structure developed by legendary improv guru Del Close. Intended to be a solo-exercise, The Quest encourages participants to 1) step out into the world with the frame of mind that they are in when they improvise, 2) explore what happens when they approach the world with a more improvisational mindset, and 3) reflect on what was discovered during the experience and come together to share experiences and insights discovered during that process through casual conversation and storytelling.
name: The Quest: Where Will Your Day Take You-Copenhagen Edition

description:
We'd like to welcome you to our FREE weekly Sahaja Yoga meditation meetings. We are all volunteers of a Charity organisation and have many years of experience in offering free Sahaja Yoga Meditation classes. All the meetings and classes are free of any charge. Each week we go through simple meditation techniques, often with guided meditations to help reduce stress and achieve the peace of true meditation. We share tips on how to help stay in balance during the day and how to meditate at home. The meditation is based on connecting with the inner chakras (energy centres) and balancing the subtle body. The tradition and aims of meditation are explained which in essence is to be in the present with no mental activity or thoughts about the past or the future. The classes are designed to help those attending get into a genuine meditative state, which can be felt tangibly. It is quite effortless and spontaneous. The free classes feature introductory talks, videos, practical workshops and general question and answer opportunities, making them perfect for seekers trying to establish a state of yoga. The idea is that you don't do yoga - you Achieve Yoga! Sahaja Yoga Meditation is a simple technique. It helps those who enjoy it, reduce stress and increase wellness. It brings better focus and helps people become more centered and better balanced. Anyone can do it. Founded by Shri Mataji Nirmala Devi, Sahaja Yoga Meditation is a world wide movement for peace and self awakening. All across the globe, many are seeking new sources of energy. Meanwhile, the most transformative energy of all is hiding in plain sight, within us. It's natural, sustainable, and infinitely renewable. It's called inner kundalini energy. And everyone already has it — everyone! It is often likened to an inner feminine or motherly energy which automatically knows about us and what is needed to help us restore balance and harmony within our subtle being. It works spontaneously, effortlessly, organically and cannot be paid for. 

http://sahajayoga.dk/ 

http://www.freemeditation.com/ 

http://www.sahajayoga.org/worldwidecontacts/


You can also find us at https://www.facebook.com/sahajayogadk/

Copenhagen Expat Yoga, Meditation and Wellness is a group for everyone who is into or wants an introduction to the wonderful world of yoga and meditation.
If you want to be in touch with your body and mind, be in the present moment, and experience a relaxing and empowering time, then look no further. There is a wide range of classes and workshops available, from Hatha, to Vinyasa, to Pre- and post-natal, to restorative yoga, as well as beginner meditation.
The sessions are taught in English (there is also a possibility for teaching in French) and are open to anyone, regardless of age, gender, skills and experience. Just come with an open mind.
Sessions can be held privately or as a group.
I am a Yoga Alliance 200 hour certified yoga teacher and I started this group to share my passion for yoga and mediation with other expats. Each session is affordable and of high quality.
Looking forward to sharing a practice with you. Namaste.

description:
For six years I struggled with an 'incurable illness' that had debilitated my life. I did not want to take the tablets that the doctors were trying to give me to suppress the problem. I wanted to know the cause, and this created a relentless search for true health and happiness. 

I obsessively read many books on the power of self healing. I saw a noticeable change within myself through implementing much of what I had learned, but I was still not fully recovered or happy within myself. I decided to quit my lucrative career in sales, sell all of my belongings and travel the world. 

For three years I deepened my understanding of myself and life. I became qualified in several different alternative healing modalities including: Theta Healing, Emotional Freedom Technique, and Matrix Re-Imprinting. I also studied hypnotherapy, psychology and Neuro Linguistic Programming. I spent months in meditation retreats, worked with a shaman in the middle of the amazon drinking plant medicine and was able to use all that I had learned to heal my chronic fatigue health issues. 

This momentum that was created drove me deeper and deeper into my own conditioning. This process / experience enabled me to wake up to clearly see the illusionary self that I had been identified with. I was then able to let go of that self layer by layer to uncover ME. Through my own pain I was able to find my passion and purpose. 

My life is now dedicated to helping other people who are searching for more happiness and well being. Working with close to 1000 individual people has given me the knowledge of why we are not living a life aligned with who we truly are. 

Through the realization of who we are NOT we are naturally taken back to who we ARE. You are NOT your limitations, you are NOT your insecurities and you are most certainly NOT your FEARS. I now host regular workshop experiences to help guide people back to their true selves. 

I look forward to being part of your evolution and expansion.

Much love Richard

Read, learn & evolve!

Personal Growth Book Club, is the first club of its kind in Copenhagen, which offers a space for individuals interested in personal growth to meet, discuss and together explore self-improvement related topics. A best seller book (potentially a TED Talk) provides a starting point for discussion, and members are encouraged to share thoughts about the book as well their own experiences with challenges they may have faced.

Meeting Time & Place:
Every month on a Thursday, 6-8pm
Copenhagen Main Library

A symbolic, one-off signup fee of 50 kr. that goes towards covering the cost of running the  group.

description:
Anyone who is interested in Mindfulness and meditation are welcome to our courses and workshops. All our courses focus both on theory and practice, so that you can have a complete understanding of the concept. Participants of our Mindfulness courses learn how to:
• decrease mind wandering
• live in the present moment as it is
• understand and deal with difficult feelings and stress
• practice formal and informal meditation exercises
• cultivate openness, patience, trust, letting go
• develop a non-judgmental, non-striving and accepting attitude
• move forward to a more successful and balanced life and relationships
• become able to practice Mindfulness by the end of the course.

We also give you guided Mindfulness meditation audio files , so that you can go on with your practice on your own and have the chance to integrate what you have learnt at the course into your daily practice!

For more information please visit our website www.mindfulnessworkshops.dk

ABOUT THE TEACHER:
Esen Sekerkarar Hansen is a Mindfulness instructor, certified NLP therapist and international speaker in the areas of self development, spirituality and consciousness. She has attended the Mindfulness teacher training pathway of University of Massachussets, where Jon Kabat-Zinn established the Center for Mindfulness. She has been organising international conferences and workshops since 1998. She continues to teach and lecture internationally.

description:
We get makeovers for our looks and appearance – but what we sometimes need the most is a life upgrade. An upgrade on how we spend our time, how we behave in our relationships, how we think, how we treat our bodies, money, and – well, basically our full life.

Many of us live life on automatic pilot and don’t feel truly excited about life. We know there can be more to life. Luckily, it’s not that difficult to shape up our lives and create a life we’re excited about. It’s never too late. Let' get together and help each other upgrade our everyday lives! On each meeting, I'll open with a presentation and share some ideas relevant to that topic. There will be time to hang out and get to know each other and have a good time!


Come, join us! Everybody is welcome!


I look forward to meeting you!

Warmly,
Tina


PS: We all know that a number of people saying they will attend a Meetup event most often doesn't reflect a number of people who actually show up. So by adding a small fee, I'll try to make it easier to plan each meeting. Thanks for your understanding.

Detoxdiet fyra veckor:

Inga produkter med raffinerade sockerarter och inget vitt mjöl. Vad vi ska ha i oss för att rensa:

Mycket vatten, grönte, paul D'arco te, fiberrika grönsaker, bär, frukt; lite frön och nötter, naturliga proteiner av fisk och fågel, fullkorns kolhydrater som quinoa, vildris, sötpotatis, nyttiga fetter som olivolja, linfröolja, kokosfett, avokado.

Börja redan nu dra ner på raffinerade produkter.

description:
This is the third of the five independent training sessions!

Objectives:

* An introduction to the Drexler / Sibbet Team Performance Model ™ and the underlying principles of process theory

* To understand how your profile and you position on the Insights Discovery wheel can contribute to the team performance

* To understand how the team members position can contribute to the team performance

* Try some team exercises to train communication and problem solving for better results

Outcome:

* Increased self-awareness and understanding of your own development and skills needs

* Initiated action plan for own development

* Tools and methods to strengthen your own communication, role and activities

Facilitation style

Start and end point is the participants' situation, where everyone will share knowledge for the benefit of the whole team. Participants are expected to bring their own experiences into the room and to actively participate in all aspects of the course. Our focus is to enable the participants by maintaining a high energy level throughout the day, where we use humour, play, imagination and creativity exercises to ensure engagement and learning.

Price (lunch is not include):

Free for JCI Malmö NK project group

200 kr for JCI and AIESEC members

250 kr for others
We are looking forward to see you all and make the most of this day!!

Read more about JCI Malmö here: https://www.jcimalmo.com/

Register for this event here: https://jcimalmo.enkelanmalan.se/15/

category.name: health/wellbeing
description:
Personal transformation is bringing workability to areas of your life that you care about; Those are not working or not working as well as you like. That is it.

Benefits include: Being yourself in ALL situations. Creating your own life that works for YOU.

--

This is a group about personal transformation. Share what is important to you to the group. Offer and receive support. Find what energizes you in life. Bring more of that into your world. Identify what drains you in life. Bring less of that into your world.

The practice requires your active participation. The results are boundless.

--------------------------------

INSPIRATION INCLUDES...

We draw inspiration from many sources. Please post your own suggestions too :)

Simple Formula For Living...

• Be your word. Admit it when you make a mistake. 

• Blame no one. Accept what they are. Accept what they are not. Don't argue. 

• Blame nothing.  Accept what is. Accept what is not. Don't make excuses.  

• Strive for excellence, not perfection. 

The Book: The Four Agreements...

• 1. Be Impeccable with your Word. Speak with integrity. Say only what you mean. Avoid using the Word to speak against yourself or to gossip about others. Use the power of your Word in the direction of truth and love.

• 2. Don’t Take Anything Personally. Nothing others do is because of you. What others say and do is a projection of their own reality, their own dream. When you are immune to the opinions and actions of others, you won’t be the victim of needless suffering.

• 3. Don’t Make Assumptions. Find the courage to ask questions and to express what you really want. Communicate with others as clearly as you can to avoid misunderstandings, sadness and drama. With just this one agreement, you can completely transform your life.

• 4. Always Do Your Best. Your best is going to change from moment to moment; it will be different when you are healthy as opposed to sick. Under any circumstance, simply do your best, and you will avoid self-judgment, self-abuse, and regret.

description:
This is a group for anyone interested in yoga & meditation/mindfulness, mind-body connection, personal development through the practice of yoga, as well as anyone eager to deepen their practice of yoga/meditation both "on the mat" and off the mat". Let's build an awesome community ("kula") centered around integrity, heart virtues, and life celebration.

Yoga can have tremendous, powerful effects on one's own development, mind-body-heart connection, and awakening process. If you're curious about or love a form of yoga practice that is non-dogmatic, heart-centered, relevant to the modern world we live in, and strong on healthy body alignment, please stay tuned and get in touch. I am life & business coach, and certified yoga & meditation instructor based in Copenhagen. I am the only teacher in Europe certified in Ashaya Yoga (®) and trained in different mindfulness-based and body-oriented personal development modalities with recognized teachers in the US and Europe. (read more about me at www.heartwiseyoga.com)

A French native and resident of Denmark for more than 8 years, I previously lived in California and the UK. I love meeting open-minded folks from diverse places and backgrounds, nature, chilling out, learning from every situation, and sharing my passion with the world. And, of course, living the yoga life.

For more info, blog posts, and free meditation samples visit my website www.heartwiseyoga.com or connect at facebook.com/heartwiseyoga.

I'll post about upcoming yoga events and retreats, mindful walks, workshops, social conscious gatherings, etc. Can't wait to embark on a self-exploratory journey with you!
Let's bring more authenticity, awareness, and heart to the world together.
Let's grow an equalitarian, conscious and heart-centered community (i.e., a "Kula") here in Copenhagen <3

Namaste Cedric

description:
Do you know what a Vision Board is? It´s a way to manifest your dream life. When you make a Vision Board, you get clear on what you want to create in your life and sell your own ideas to yourself.

Everyone from Kate Perry to Oprah swears that they intentionally created outcomes by using this simple tool. It anchors in your dreams and allows the magic of manifestation to work in your life. 

It sounds pretty simple, but there is a process to make Vision Boards more powerful which is what I will be showing you. So, why doesn't everyone do this? Well, in my experience as a trainer, most of us never take the time. We let our busy, distracted lives keep us, well, busy and distracted.

It`s time to change that. On Saturday, April 21st,  from 9:30 - 4:30,  I am hosting a Create Your Life Vision Board Workshop. It´s a full day immersion for you to focus on your authentic life, core clarity and ideal outcomes. The price of the full day workshop is 450 danish kroner. 

The location is in Sluseholm, Copenhagen. You can contact me for more details by sending an email to mtgchristoffersen@gmail.com and I will send you all the information! Can´t wait! Therese

description:
We all crave for being seen and heard beyond judgment.
We all long for self-expression. We all long for authentic connection.

Are you a woman or man and you recognize yourself in these statements?
Come and join our Secret Space that will take the form of a circle.

Structure: We are starting the circle 15.00. The door will be open from 14.50.
90 minutes of circling. After the circle is finished, coffee/tea and space for social mingling until 17.00.

What is Circling?

category.name: health/wellbeing
description: Mahatma Gandhi once said about meditation, "I have an extremely busy day today, and I have such little time to do everything! I need to do double the meditation to cope with it." He was one of the few who knew that meditation increases one's efficiency and productivity, and meditated every single day. ​Competition is at its highest, and being innovative and productive is more important than ever today. Employees who work hard and devote more and more time to being productive end up becoming very stressed. A stressful mind will never be productive or creative. If this was the case, most of the frustrated, stressed-out, unemployed youth would be very creative or innovative. This is not the case. Creativity and innovation can only come from a relaxed mind. Similarly, productivity can only come from deep rest. This seems contradictory. How can you rest when you have tonnes of work to complete? Just like in order to hit an arrow on a target, the arrow must first be pulled backward, in the same way, to be more efficient at work, some amount of time must be spent in meditation, i.e., doing nothing, but relaxing effortlessly. This is the key to get more work done in less time, and keep stress at bay. I Meditate Malmö is a movement empowering Malmoers to do more of the things they love by recharging through meditation: a practical way to refresh every day, invented thousands of years ago. Reinvented in 2014. 'I Meditate' is an initiative of the US Art of Living chapter. Some other cities/places where free meditation is offered under "I Meditate" are: 1. New York, USA - http://www.imeditateny.org/ 2. Calgary, Canada - http://imeditatecalgary.org/ 3. Washington DC, USA - http://imeditatedc.org/ 4. Africa - http://www.artofliving.org/i-meditate-africa 5. Gothenburg, Sweden - https://www.facebook.com/IMeditateGBG 6. Stockholm, Sweden
name: I Meditate Malmö

description:
This is the third of the five independent training sessions!

Objectives:

* An introduction to the Drexler / Sibbet Team Performance Model ™ and the underlying principles of process theory

* To understand how your profile and you position on the Insights Discovery wheel can contribute to the team performance

* To understand how the team members position can contribute to the team performance

* Try some team exercises to train communication and problem solving for better results

Outcome:

* Increased self-awareness and understanding of your own development and skills needs

* Initiated action plan for own development

* Tools and methods to strengthen your own communication, role and activities

Facilitation style

Start and end point is the participants' situation, where everyone will share knowledge for the benefit of the whole team. Participants are expected to bring their own experiences into the room and to actively participate in all aspects of the course. Our focus is to enable the participants by maintaining a high energy level throughout the day, where we use humour, play, imagination and creativity exercises to ensure engagement and learning.

Price (lunch is not include):

Free for JCI Malmö NK project group

200 kr for JCI and AIESEC members

250 kr for others
We are looking forward to see you all and make the most of this day!!

Read more about JCI Malmö here: https://www.jcimalmo.com/

Register for this event here: https://jcimalmo.enkelanmalan.se/15/

description:
We'd like to welcome you to our FREE weekly Sahaja Yoga meditation meetings.

We are all volunteers of a Charity organisation and have many years of experience in offering free Sahaja Yoga Meditation classes. All the meetings and classes are free of any charge. Each week we go through simple meditation techniques, often with guided meditations to help reduce stress and achieve the peace of true meditation. We share tips on how to help stay in balance during the day and how to meditate at home.

The meditation is based on connecting with the inner chakras (energy centres) and balancing the subtle body. The tradition and aims of meditation are explained which in essence is to be in the present with no mental activity or thoughts about the past or the future. The classes are designed to help those attending get into a genuine meditative state, which can be felt tangibly. It is quite effortless and spontaneous.

The free classes feature introductory talks, videos, practical workshops and general question and answer opportunities, making them perfect for seekers trying to establish a state of yoga. The idea is that you don't do yoga - you Achieve Yoga!

Sahaja Yoga Meditation is a simple technique. It helps those who enjoy it, reduce stress and increase wellness. It brings better focus and helps people become more centered and better balanced. Anyone can do it.

Founded by Shri Mataji Nirmala Devi, Sahaja Yoga Meditation is a world wide movement for peace and self awakening. All across the globe, many are seeking new sources of energy. Meanwhile, the most transformative energy of all is hiding in plain sight, within us. It's natural, sustainable, and infinitely renewable. It's called inner kundalini energy. And everyone already has it — everyone! It is often likened to an inner feminine or motherly energy which automatically knows about us and what is needed to help us restore balance and harmony within our subtle being. It works spontaneously, effortlessly, organically and cannot be paid for.

http://www.sahajayoga.se

http://www.freemeditation.com/

http://www.sahajayoga.org/worldwidecontacts/

You can find us allso at Facebook https://www.facebook.com/Sahajayogagothenburg

description:
Quantified Self is about measuring yourself with sensors, apps and other technology to collect data and make that data useful through visualisation and other ways of feedback.


 If you are interested in body measurement in particular and sensors and emerging technology in general this is the place to be. 

This group is about sharing ideas, solutions and data and to learn more through this collaboration. To get more inspiration about Quantified Self, watch this 5-minute TEDx talk by Gary Wolf, the co-founder of Quantified Self: http://www.ted.com/talks/gary_wolf_the_quantified_self#t-3843

The Quantified Self Show&Tell is a regular meeting for people taking advantage of various kinds of personal tracking to gain more knowledge about themselves. We use the show&tell format you learned as a child: stand up and present something you care about, take questions, and sit down. It is usually very fun. Come share what you are doing, and learn from others. Topics include, but are not limited to:

Fitness and health tracking
Chemical body load counts
Personal genome sequencing
Lifelogging
Metabolic monitoring
Self experimentation
Behavior monitoring
Location tracking
Sleep tracking
Mood and emotion tracking
Medical self-diagnostics

The Quantified Self meetup is associated with Quantified Self organization and is  about self knowledge through numbers at http://www.quantifiedself.org. 

Your hosts are Peter Nordin. 

I have my own blogg called www.4success.se Write me with your recommendations, tips, and observations (peter at 4success dot se).

description:
Söker du motivation och inspiration för att ta nästa steg i karriären? Funderar Du på att byta jobb? Är Du inne på att starta eget bolag? Funderar Du på att byta inriktning i din befintliga verksamhet? Funderar Du på vilken utbildning Du ska påbörja?

Gruppen är till för dig som vill träffa upp andra människor för att inspireras, motiveras och utbyta erfarenheter.

Du som medlem kan vara allt ifrån en super entreprenör till en arbetssökande. Syftet med träffarna är att jobba med den personliga utvecklingen, Du kommer att få en del små tips och tricks på hur Du når personlig utveckling tillsammans med andra som söker samma sak. Vi kommer att följa varandras utveckling, bjuda in inspiratörer, utvecklas i en motiverande miljö. Du kommer garanterat att få en spark i baken.

Vi träffas en gång i månaden på Barken Viking (Lilla Bommens Torg 10).

category.name: health/wellbeing
description:
Welcome to a new book club in Gothenburg. Not your ordinary book club. We are reading together a book each month. It will be a book which can shift something in our minds, or can teach us something new we always wanted to learn about or can give us that little kick we needed to get that project started... Yeah, you got it, books about creativity, motivation, mind, well-being, happiness, relationships, innovations, entrepreneurship and future of work.

When the rebels get together they enjoy not only the inspiring discussions but also a delightful treat - it can be a wine, a cocktail or a delicious chocolate cake, depending on the season and on the book. Details will follow closer to the dates.

Here is a list of the awesome books the rebels have read so far:

• February - "The Chimp Paradox" by Steve Peters on mindset and relationships

• March -  "Steal Like an Artist: 10 Things Nobody Told You About Being Creative" by Austin Kleon on creativity

• April - "The 4-Hour Workweek: Escape 9-5, Live Anywhere, and Join the New Rich" by Tim Ferriss on productivity and entrepreneurship 

• May - "The War of Art" by Steven Pressfield on resistance, fears and just doing the work.

• June - "Wonder" by R.J. Palacio. A book about friendship, love, courage and challenges. An easy read about very powerful aspects of our lives.

• August - "The Willpower Instinct: How Self-Control Works, Why It Matters, and What You Can Do to Get More of It" by Kelly McGonigal. 

• September / October - "Hacking Growth: How Today's Fastest-Growing Companies Drive Breakout Success" by Sean Ellis and Morgan Brown. 

This is not only a “book of the month” book club, it is also a space where we can brainstorm, spread ideas, share knowledge and hold each other accountable for the actions we wish to take.

Join the group, spread the word, get going!
name: Better Read This Book Club

description:
Warmly welcome to weekly Monday meditation sessions at Föreningen för Tibetansk Buddhism i Göteborg - FFTB (Association for Tibetan Buddhism in Gothenburg), throughout the year. 


FFTB is a non-profit organisation, that has been established in 1994. We are regularly inviting Buddhist teachers from all four traditions of Tibetan Buddhism and arrange meditation retreats, weekend courses, public talks and many other activities.

http://tibetanskbuddhism.se/
https://www.facebook.com/Tibetansk-Buddhism-i-Göteborg-147244568659059/

*new* check out our youtube channel at
https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCtI_hPwsdKloN0cntNpIzIA

We have stillness (shamatha) meditation sessions every Monday between 19.00 and 20.15 at Linnégatan 21 in Gothenburg. It is open for everyone interested in meditation.
This Monday meditation sessions are free, we would though appreciate a small donation (20 SEK) to contribute to the rent.

Welcome!

description: Corybantic Muse means a wild and unrestrained source of inspiration. My mission, if you will, is to inspire you on your quest to create and maintain an incredible life. This means looking at the arenas of your lifestyle, relationships, love, spirituality, and health and wellness to decide what is working for you and what you may be interested in shifting in changing to create an even more incredible life. I see life as a quest of finding your way through your own Wonderland that you are fully in control of and shift or change when you are ready. This means getting curious about your who, what, when, where, and why. That does not mean that bad things will never happen in your life, but that you choose how you respond and deal with those things just like you do with the good things that occur. There is no right or wrong way to do life, there is just different. Each new opportunity presented is yet another rabbit hole you can say yes or no to. Would you like to join me and other like-minded people on this adventure?
name: Corybantic Muse
